Time for the final innings of this game! England have a massive task in front of them. The Indian players are in a huddle near the ropes. They disperse in the field now. Dom Sibley and Rory Burns will open the innings for England. 20 overs before Stumps. Ishant Sharma will start off for India. He struck in the first innings in the first over. Here he goes again.

It is not going to be easy but Kohli and Ashwin showed that you can always score runs once you dig in and apply yourself, you can bat long and score runs. However, the English batters will be against the might of Ashwin and others. So, a tricky phase for the England batters. The 4th innings will begin shortly.

England worked hard with the ball throughout but they were not consistent with the lines and lengths. Indians, in spite of losing quick wickets in the first session, did well to score over 100 runs. And then Kohli and Ashwin extended the lead in the 2nd session to force England completely on the back foot. After Ashwin got to his ton, Siraj smoked a couple of sixes before Ashwin dragged one on his stumps. And, now, England have a big target to chase on this deck which has been turning square from Day 1.

Right! India have been bowled out. Ashwin walks back along with Siraj with a standing ovation from the crowd. A brilliant batting performance from the Indians! Kohli fell in the second session but the man with a fifer in the first innings continued. He batted superbly in this session and with fine support from Siraj, he reached a scintillating century to power India to a huge lead.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! End of a fantastic innings and that will also be the end of India's innings. Ashwin's superb knock comes to an end and he walks off to a standing ovation, one which he rightfully deserves. Shortish ball just outside off, Ashwin looks to pull it on the leg side but gets a thick inside edge which sees the ball hit the stumps. INDIA ALL OUT FOR 286! ENGLAND NEED 482 TO WIN!
Shorter on off, Ashwin pulls it to mid on.
Good length ball around off, Ashwin punches it through the off side and gets a couple.
Fuller on off, Ashwin pushes it to mid off.
On the stumps, Ash blocks it.
Darted fuller on off, Siraj now shows good defensive technique and blocks it.
SIX! Cracking shot! Siraj is having a party at the moment. Leach is the one paying for that party and he will not like it one bit. Floated on off, Siraj smokes his slog over mid-wicket for a biggie.
On the pads, Ashwin flicks it to the leg side and shows faith in Siraj as he takes a single.

Hits the helmet of England but does not count. Darted around leg, Ashwin looks to pad it away. It kisses his pad and then hits the helmet which is kept behind the keeper. But because Ashwin did not offer a shot, the penalty runs won't count.
Floated outside off, Siraj comes down the track and looks to defend. He ends up getting an inside edge on the pad. The ball then goes to the off side and they take one.
Shorter around off, Siraj defends it off his back foot.
Shortish ball around off, Ashwin pulls it to mid on.
Good length ball around off, Ashwin punches it to mid off.
Short ball on off and middle, Ashwin pulls it to mid on.
Full toss which is just under the waist height. It is around the pads, Ashwin manages to flick it away to deep square leg but does not take the single.
Good shot but well fielded. Full outside off, Ashwin drives it to the left of cover. The fielder there dives and saves runs for his side.
Full on off, Ashwin defends it calmly.
Olly Stone is back.
Full and around middle and leg, Siraj plays the helicopter shot. Root at mid-wicket dives to his left and looks to catch but fails to hold on. They do not go for the single.
Floated full and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Just short. This one is short and around off and middle, Siraj defends it off his back foot. Not from the middle and it lobs short of the man at short leg.

SIX! How about that? How about that? What an amazing blow. One for the ages from Siraj. Leach tosses it up again. This time Siraj stays in the crease and powers it over long on for a biggie. Kohli loves it in the dressing room.
Flat and just around off, solidly blocked.

Siraj is off the mark now! He is done with showing all the patience. Ashwin has got to the milestone and now Siraj wants to have some fun. Goes for the massive slog as Leach tosses it up and around off, he mistimes it off the inner half towards deep square leg for a brace.
FOUR LEG BYES! Darted quicker around leg, Ashwin looks to sweep but the ball goes off his pads down the leg side and to the fence.

HUNDRED FOR ASHWIN! What a player! What an innings! The man with the ball has also done the job with the bat! Take a bow, sir! This is top quality knock. Floated delivery around off, Ashwin looks to go over on the off side but it goes off the outside edge over the slips and races away to the fence at third man. Ashwin sprints to the other end, removes his helmet and jumps in the air in pure jubilation. The crowd is on its feet as their local superstar has followed a 5-fer with an extraordinary ton. Siraj punches the air as well. Looked like he is happier than Ashwin is. Not an easy pitch to bat on but Ashwin has shown his class, temperament and technique to get a ton. All his teammates are on their feet as they know this is one of the best innings they have witnessed. 5th Test ton for the local lad.
Make that 99! Ashwin now just one away from what would be an outstanding century. Flighted on off, Ashwin drives it away from sweeper cover and gets a brace.

SIX! Going, going, gone! That was six the moment it left the bat. Floated on off, Ashwin gets down on his knees and smokes his sweep over mid-wicket for a biggie. The sound it made as soon as it hit the bat was indication enough to know that was out of here. Ashwin moves to 97 now. The lead crosses 450.
Floated on off, Ashwin pushes it to mid off.

This is the loudest cheer you could possibly hear. Siraj has taken a single. Floated on off, Siraj defends it square on the off side. He is holding his pose but Ashwin calls for a run and they get it with ease. Siraj has a huge smile on his face as he looks at Ashwin.
No he cannot! Siraj will face the next over. Darted fuller around middle and leg, Aswin sweeps it but straight to short fine leg.
FOUR! Nicely played! 250 up for India and Ashwin moves to the 90s! Short and spinning away, Ashwin cuts it nicely away from point and gets a boundary. Can he farm the strike now?
Flighted on middle, Ashwin drives it straight down the ground but does not take the single.
Tossed up on the stumps, Ashwin blocks it.
Turn and bounce on this one. It pitches on the rough around off. Ashwin looks to defend but the ball turns away and beats the outside edge.
Floated on off, Ashwin pushes it ti cover.
Second new ball is available now. And England have opted it. Leach will continue though.
Fired short and around off, Siraj negotiates it with ease this time. And the crowd approves the same again.
Floated outside off, spins in after landing on the rough. Siraj comes on the front foot to defend but the ball spins in to hit him high on the pad.
Darted around off, Siraj is solid on the back foot defense. The crowd loves it as well.
He drops it quick and just around off, Siraj stays and blocks.
Tossed on the pads, Ashwin looks to play the reverse sweep. Gets an under edge and the ball goes very close to the stumps. Goes to fine leg and Ashwin crosses. Moeen has 4 balls to Siraj now.
Floated outside off, kept out.
Siraj survives! A huge respite for the crowd as they want to see their local hero to get a ton. Floated on off, Siraj defends it.
Floated on off, Siraj defends it off the front foot.
Floated around off, Siraj looks to defend but gets beaten.
Another roar from the crowd as Siraj blocks this shortish ball off his back foot.
Huge cheer from the crowd as Siraj blocks it. Shorter on middle, Siraj defends it.
Beaten! Tossed up on middle, Siraj looks to defend but the ball turns away and squares up Siraj as it goes past his outside edge.
Darted fuller on off, Ashwin blocks it. Leach can have a crack at Siraj in the next over.

IN THE AIR...AND FOUR!  Good effort in the deep but the ball falls well short of the fielder. Floated around off, Ashwin connects well with the sweep this time. It goes high in the air and away to the left of deep backward square leg. The fielder there dives and gets his hands on the ball after the bounce. He though is unable to stop it and can just deflect it to the fence.
Ohh! Floated around off, Ashwin looks to sweep but it hits the bottom edge and stays on the off side of the pitch.
Shorter on off, Ashwin punches it back to the bowler.
Short on off, Ashwin defends it.
On the stumps, RA blocks.
Around off, Ashwin dabs it to third man and gets a single to keep the strike.
FOUR! Short and punished! It is on middle, Ashwin pulls it, and unlike the first ball of the over, this time he pulls it hard and in the gap for a boundary.
Mohammed Siraj is the last man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Leach gets his fourth and the bowling change has worked for England. Flighted delivery on off, Ishant looks to go for a big hoick with a slog sweep. He does not connect it as it comes off the upper half of his bat. Stone at square leg, runs to his left and slides to take a very good catch. 9 down and Ashwin is unbeaten on 77. Can Siraj hang in there till Ashwin's century?
Flighted on middle, Ishant looks to defend and does so off the outer half of his bat.
Tossed up on off, Ishant defends it.
Leach starts with a shorter delivery on middle and leg, Ashwin pulls it off his back foot to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Jack Leach is back on. 28-5-74-3 from him so far.
Slightly shorter on off, Ishant defends it off his back foot.
On the stumps, kept out by Ishant.
On the pads, Ishant turns it behind square leg for a brace.
Darted quicker and fuller outside off, Ishant looks to sweep but misses. There is a stifled appeal but the impact was well outside off.
FOUR! Ishant is taking on the bowlers as well now. Flighted on off, Ishant comes down the track and lifts it over cow corner for a boundary.
Darted full on off, Ishant jams it out.
Ishant takes a single and gets off the mark in this Test. On the pads, Ishant flicks it to the leg side and keeps the strike with one.
On the pads, Ashwin once again takes the aggressive route and flicks it over square leg. There is protection in the deep so just a run.

FOUR! The ploy looks clear, Ashwin is trying to get to his century as quickly as possible and then India might declare. Fuller around off, Ashwin goes over mid off and gets a boundary. The local boy moves to 75 with that.
On off, kept out.
Full on off, Ashwin pushes it to cover.
Broad starts with a fuller ball on off and middle, Ashwin defends it to mid on.
Who will partner Ali from the other end to begin the final session? Stuart Broad it is.
Well defended. Flighted around off, the ball keeps low but Ishant keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it late off his back foot.

In the air but in no man's land. Tossed up on off, Ashwin comes down the track and looks to go over on the on side. He does not time it well but gets a lot of height on it. Luckily for the local lad, the ball falls between the fielder coming in from the deep and the one running behind. Single taken.
Floated on off, Ashwin blocks it.

Stumping opportunity missed! Foakes, who has been brilliant in this game has missed a stumping. Floated delivery outside off, Ashwin comes down the track and looks to go big but misses. The ball keeps low and kind of wrong-foots Foakes. He is unable to get down and collect the ball. There is a noise and Ultra Edge later shows that there was a little spike as the ball went past the bottom edge of the bat. A tough chance but from what we have seen from Foakes in this Test, he will be gutted to have missed that.
First runs of the session! Short around off, Ashwin punches it through extra cover and gets a couple.
Moeen starts with a floated delivery on the pad. Ashwin flicks it to square leg.

We are back for the final session of Day 3. Ravichandran Ashwin and Ishant Sharma stride out to resume their innings. The England players are out in the middle as well. Moeen Ali with the ball first up. One shy of a fifer. Here we go...
... Day 3, Session 3 ...

Once again it was tough work for England. They did manage to slow down the scoring rate slightly but failed to bundle out India. Joe Root tried all his options and even gave an extended spell to Stuart Broad but to no avail. Moeen has a 4-wicket haul to his name now as he picked both the wickets to fall in the afternoon session. He has toiled very hard and would love to pick a fifer. Do join us at 1430 local (0900 GMT) for the evening session.

Yet another session of cracking action! Virat Kohli and Ravichandran Ashwin extended their partnership and kept the English team at bay. Both got to their fifties and then Kohli was consumed by Moeen Ali for the fifth time in Test cricket. The 7th wicket stand though has cornered the touring team as India now lead by a massive 416 runs and still have two wickets in the bank.
Full and wide outside off, Ishant keeps it out nicely. With this, IT IS TEA ON DAY 3.
Short and wide outside off, Ashwin dabs it down to third man for a single.
Broad bowls a fine yorker but Ashwin is ready for it. He digs it out nicely.
Shortish and around middle, Ashwin works it to deep mid-wicket. Says no for the run.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards point.
Outside off on a good length, Ashwin looks to defend but is beaten on the inside edge.
Looped up and outside off, driven to mid off for nothing. Ishant sees off another Moeen over.

Appeal from the keeper but nothing from Moeen. He feels it would've gone over. This one pitches outside off and spins in. Ishant is on the back foot. He looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. An appeal but turned down.
Full and outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flat and around off, Ishant goes back to block.
Around off, Ishant is solid in defense this time.
Floated around off, turns in. Ishant looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and goes to the leg side.

FOUR! Quality shot! Ravichandran Ashwin is showing his full repertoire. A lovely on drive from his blade. Full and on middle, Ashwin brings down a straight bat and creams it over mid on for a boundary. India lead by 415 runs.
Fuller length ball on middle and leg, Ashwin tries to flick but misses.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Ashwin remains on the back foot and mistimes his punch back to the bowler.
Length ball on middle and off, Ashwin covers the line and offers a straight bat in defense.
A length delivery on middle and leg, Ashwin helps it behind square leg and returns for the second run.
Good length ball around off, Ashwin punches it off his back foot to deepish mid off. No run taken.
Too full in length and on off, Ishant jams it out on the deck.
Silly point comes in.
Full and flighted on off, Ishant is nicely forward as he defends it with soft hands.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Skidding away from the batsman, again on the shorter side but staying low, Ishant brings his bat down and keeps it out off the outer edge.
Flatter and a touch short on off, Sharma defends it off his back foot.
Very full and on off, Sharma digs it out off the inner half to leg gully.
Outside off on a good length, Ashwin pokes it towards backward point. Thinks for a single but Ishant says no as it went to the fielder quickly.
Length ball around off, once again Ashwin is right behind the line in defense.
Good length and around off, Ashwin blocks it this time.

FOUR LEG BYES! Good length and outside off, Ashwin moves inside the crease and looks to paddle it over the keeper. Ashwin misses and the ball hits the keeper's leg and goes to the fine leg fence. Given leg byes.
The ball is being checked by the umpire. Broad is not happy with the seam which has come off.
Around off on a length. Ashwin is solid in defense.
Short and wide outside off, Ashwin plays it to third man. Denies the single.
Ishant Sharma joins Ravichandran Ashwin in the middle.
Time for another review! Kuldeep Yadav has been adjudged lbw and he looks like a sitting duck. Still decides to review it. All reds, Kuldeep is on his bike.

OUT! LBW! Three reds and Moeen has his 4th. Fuller and around off and middle, Kuldeep comes on the front foot and looks to defend but this one doesn't turn much. He though plays for it and misses to get hit on the pad. An appeal is made and the umpire has no problem raising his finger. It looked out but Kuldeep takes the review. Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows no bat. Time for the Ball Tracker. Here it comes. Pitching in line, impact in line and hitting the wickets. So, Kuldeep has to go. 8 down for India.
Beaten this time! Lovely from Moeen. Lands it middle and leg on the rough. Spins away to beat the outside edge.
Lovely drive! Tossed up and outside off, driven through the covers for a brace. Kuldeep is no mug with the bat, has a First Class hundred to his name.
Floated around off, Kuldeep keeps it out nicely once more.
On middle once again, Kuldeep blocks it by drawing forward.
Floated on middle, solidly defended by Kuldeep.
Length ball around middle, Kuldeep tucks it through square leg for a run.
Pokes this one through the covers and gets to the other end now.
FOUR! Nicely done! Insult to the injury. This is just outside off on a good length. Ashwin waits and then nicely opens the face of the bat to run it down to the third man fence. The lead crosses 400.

Dropped! Foakes is the man. Such a good work from him so far but when the edge is drawn, Foakes fails to hold on. A rare miss from him. This is around off on a good length, Ashwin looks to guide it late but ends up getting a thick outside edge. It goes little right of Foakes who gets his gloves to it but fails to hold on.
Fullish and around off, played back to the bowler.
Good length and around off, Ashwin blocks.
Floated on middle, Kuldeep blocks it off the front foot. Successful over from Moeen.
Floated around off, Yadav pushes it to mid off.
Who walks in next? It is Kuldeep Yadav.
DRS time! Virat Kohli is given out LBW and he takes the review. Is it too high? Ultra Edge finds no bat and the Ball Tracker shows it to be the umpire's call on hitting the wickets.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets and Moeen has got his man again. Kohli has to depart. It is the 5th time that Moeen has got the better of Kohli in Tests. This is floated around off, slightly short. It spins in. Kohli looks to work it on the leg side from the back foot but misses to get struck on the pad. A loud appeal follows and the finger goes up. Kohli has a chat with his partner and then signals the 'T'. Replays roll in. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Ball Tracker rolls in. It is umpire's call on hitting the wickets. So, the on-field call will stay. A brilliant, brilliant knock from the Indian skipper on this turning track comes to an end. The 96-run stand is broken and India lead by 397 runs.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
Tossed up and outside off, eased through the covers for one now.
Extra bounce there. It floats on off and spins in with extra bounce. Ashwin manages to defend off his back foot.
Just outside off and on a good length. VK has his sticks covered as he lets it go to Foakes again. A sharp take from him again.
Outside off, left alone by Virat. Broad has a smile on his face.
Around off on a length, pushed to backward point for nothing.
Broad goes fuller and around off, Kohli defends it easily this time.
Outside off this time and Kohli lets it be. Foakes fails to collect it cleanly this time.
Good length and outside off, fingers rolled. Kohli looks to defend but misses to connect. Good from Foakes once again behind the wickets.
Floated on middle, Kohli flicks it to deep mid-wicket and takes one to keep the strike for the next over.
Short and turning in, Ashwin works it through square leg and gets to the other end. 200 up for the hosts. The lead is now 395.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed to mid off for nothing by Ashwin.
On middle, this time he flicks it through square leg and moves to 61.
Full and wide outside off, Kohli looks to play the big-booming drive through the covers but fails to middle it well and finds the fielder.
Full toss outside off, swept to deep mid-wicket for one.
Shortish and just around off, Kohli stays back and blocks solidly.
Shortish in length and around off, poked towards the man at backward point.
Around off on a length, Ashwin looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes to square leg. A run taken.
Leading edge but safe. A fuller ball, Ashwin looks to work it on the leg side but he ends up getting a leading edge. The ball goes uppishly but it is wide of the fielder at short cover.
Fullish and outside off, it pitches and then moves away. Ashwin fails to put the bat on the ball. Foakes fails to collect cleanly this time. Broad rolled his fingers on this one.
Fullish and around off, Ashwin punches it solidly but Broad makes a half stop.
Stuart Broad is back on. Just 2 overs from him so far in this innings.

Drinks break. The pitch which has been termed poor by the naysayers has seen two half-centuries on Day 3. Virat Kohli and Ravichandran Ashwin are playing brilliantly at the moment and their partnership is now 90 runs. The Indian lead has swelled to 391 and England are completely cornered. Their spinners have bowled well only in patches and it's been a mixed-bag from them - some great deliveries mixed with some boundary balls. Plenty of time left in this Test match and India would like to bat long and bat England out of the match completely.
Flat and just around off, worked on the leg side.
Short and just outside off, poked towards the point region. Kohli comes ahead looking for a run but is sent back.
Shortish and around middle, spins in. Ashwin tucks it to fine leg for a run.
Floated outside off, extra bounce as well. Ashwin looks to defend by getting forward and across but misses to get bat on ball.
Full and around off, Ashwin blocks it back to the bowler.
Slower through the air and around off, turning in. Kohli nudges it wide of the man at short fine leg and takes one.
Moeen Ali is back on. 21-5-62-2 from him so far.
Short and wide outside off, punched to the cover-point region. The Indian lead is now 389 runs.
Back of a length and around middle, tucked on the leg side.
Another short ball, this one keeps a touch low. Kohli pulls. It goes off the inner half to deep square leg for one.
Banged short to Kohli as well. It is on middle, Kohli lets it go to the keeper.
Short and around off, pulled down to long on for one.
Short but down the leg side. Ashwin is expecting the shortish length. He moves inside and looks to work it on the leg side but misses.
Tossed up outside off, Kohli takes his front foot to the pitch of the ball and plays a solid push to the cover region.
Short and wide, turning away. Kohli hits it through the covers and gets two.
Floated around off, Kohli is solid in defense again.
Slightly short and just outside off, punched towards the cover fielder.
Floated full and around off, Kohli defends solidly.
Floated short and around off, kept out.
Short again but this one is down the leg side. Ashwin looks to pull but fails to connect. Foakes stops the ball to his left with a dive.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR ASHWIN! Through the off side. Ashwin is on the back foot again. Short ball outside off, he rocks back and whacks it through the covers and it races away to the fence. A fine, fine knock from the local boy. The crowd is up on its feet. His 12th Test half-ton and a very good one, coming in just 64 balls. Delivered with the ball in the first innings and is doing it with the willow here.
A cross-court forehand by Ashwin. Australian Open is going on and Ash is showing his skills here in Chennai. Stone has banged it short and Ashwin slaps it down to long on for two.
A freebie and Virat will feel he missed out there. A high full toss. He just flicks it to fine leg for one.
Good length and around off, Kohli defends it back to the bowler.
Shortish and around off, poked towards backward point.
Around off, slightly short. Ashwin is on the back foot to block.
Flat and around off, Ashwin is solid in defense.
On middle, kept out.
FOUR! Crunched! Poor from Leach. Dropped short and offered plenty of room as well. Ashwin says thank you very much and slams it through the cover-point region to bag another boundary.

Big turn! A superb take once again from Foakes. This one lands on the rough around off and middle, a big puff of dust comes off. It spins away like a cobra. Ashwin lets it be. Foakes shows his class as he collects it nicely to his right.
Floated outside off, kept out.
Short and just outside off, guided to the man at backward point.
Good length and around off, this time Kohli taps it towards the off side. Wanted a single but Ashwin says no.
Excellent running from Kohli. A shortish ball on middle, he flicks it wide of the man at fine leg. Calls for the second run and makes it easily in the end.
Fuller and on middle, clipped to the man at mid-wicket.
Fullish and around off, punched straight back to the bowler.
In the channel outside off to begin from Stone. Kohli shoulders arms.

Foakes getting some attention. He got hit on the thumb while collecting the throw on the last ball of the last over. Pops a pill and gulps down some water. Also, Root brings on Olly Stone to bowl now.

Drives it little left of the mid off fielder as Leach overpitches. Calls for a quick single and make it easily. The throw comes to the keeper and Foakes seems to have hurt himself while collecting the ball. Physio is out.
Dropped a bit short and once again Kohli pushes it to mid on off the back foot.
Goes back and plays it back to the bowler this time as Leach drops it slightly short.
Loopy and outside off, Kohli prods forward and blocks.
Full and around off, kept out off the front foot.
Tossed up and outside off, poked towards the cover region.
Short and turning in. Kohli nudges it down to deep mid-wicket for one. 5 from the over, doing it with ease.
Outside off, Ashwin comes forward, pokes it towards the off side and takes a single. Moves to 40 now.
Shortish and around middle, clipped through square leg for one.
Tossed up and wide outside off, Virat goes back and blocks it with soft hands towards short third man.
On middle, Ashwin sweeps it to deep square leg for one.

FIFTY FOR KOHLI! His 25th in the format. In testing conditions where the others around him have struggled, the Indian skipper has delivered. A fine, fine knock from him. He has risen to the occasion and showed how it is done when the wicket spins. A shortish ball, it is outside off, he goes back and works it through mid-wicket for a single. Missed out in the first innings but the Indian skipper has stood tall here. A big round of applause from everyone in the stands.
Full and around off, Ashwin is solid in defense as he draws forward.
Quicker one, it pitches and spins in sharply. Ashwin looks to defend but it takes the gloves and goes to short third man.
Quick single! A fuller one again. Kohli hits it to mid on hard but knows that the fielder is not on his heels. Takes off and completes the single easily. One shy of a brilliant half-ton.
Floated full and around off, blocked solidly by stretching forward.
Full and on middle, Ashwin flicks it to deep mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Shortish and outside off, punched towards the cover region.
Floated outside off, Kohli goes back and blocks it towards the man at mid-wicket.

FOUR! First time Kohli brings the sweep and bags a boundary. Tossed up and on middle, Kohli gets down and nails the sweep over square leg for a boundary. Moves to 48. You rarely see Virat play the sweep shot but he did practice it a lot before this Test match. Pulled it off with aplomb as well.
Shortish and on middle, worked on the leg side for one.
Muted LBW appeal. Floated around off, Kohli comes on the front foot and looks to defend. Gets an inside edge on the pad.
Pitches on middle, turns in. Kohli goes back to work it on the leg side. Fails to connect. Foakes makes a fine take down the leg side.
Ashwin comes down the track and pokes it through covers for one.
On middle, short again. Kohli easily nudges it on the leg side. Although not in the gap.
Flat and just outside off, Kohli blocks solidly.
Flat and just outside off, tucked wide of mid on for one.
Floated outside off, Ashwin this time dances down and looks to defend. Misses to get hit on the pad.
Short and outside off again. Ashwin is on the back foot to block.
Floated outside off, Ashwin keeps it out from the back foot. Does well to deal with the extra bounce there.
Fuller and around off, worked to the man at short leg.
Short again, this one is outside off, Kohli stays back to block.
Short and around middle, tucked on the leg side.
Floated around off, kept out.
FOUR! A Kohli-special this time! Full and outside off, Kohli drills it through the covers and it races away to the fence.
Turns in from outside off and hits Kohli high on the pad as he misses to defend. Too high!
Beaten this time! Turn and bounce from around off, Ashwin goes on the back foot and initially looks to push inside the line but then withdraws his bat as it spins past his blade.
Loopy but too full on off, Ashwin is forward as he defends it late.
Leach drags his length short around off and Kohli also drags his body inside the crease. He, then, punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Loopy and full, landing on middle, Kohli defends it right under his eyes.
Virat stretches forward to a full ball outside off and blocks it safely.
Tossed up ball on off, Kohli defends it solidly from the crease.
Floated and full, around off, Ashwin flicks it off the inner half of his bat to short mid-wicket.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.

Confusion over a run! Tossed up ball on middle, Ashwin is on the back foot as tickles it behind square leg. Kohli wants a run but Ashwin sends him back as the short fine leg fielder attacks the ball. There is a direct hit at the bowler's end but Virat is safely in by then.
Full and flighted outside off, Ashwin draws well forward and defends it near his front pad.
Too full and close to off, Kohli brings his bottom hand into play and drills it to long on for one.
A tossed up ball, an off spinner but on the shorter side, Ashwin hangs back and works it wide of short fine leg for a run.

We are back again! The England players stride out to the middle. Virat Kohli along with Ravichandran Ashwin make their way out to resume their innings. Moeen Ali will begin with the ball for England. Here we go...
... Day 3, Session 2 ...

After conceding a hefty lead, England are always going to be behind the 8-ball. Despite a 5-wicket session for them, they are staring down at a big deficit. For India, Virat Kohli has held one end strongly on a tough pitch and now has an able ally in Ravichandran Ashwin. Together, they have constructed a 50-run stand and the lead has now swelled to 351 runs. Another hour of batting from the current pair and the hosts would fancy their chances of declaring as anything above 400 looks next to impossible to scale down. Let's see how the afternoon session pans out. It will get underway at 1210 local (0640 GMT).

What an entertaining morning session! There were wickets galore for England but India also managed to score above 100 runs in it. The pitch, as expected, is assisting the spinners and the English tweakers made full use of it.  Cheteshwar Pujara's run out was unfortunate but after that, we witnessed some excellent bowling from the touring team and Ben Foakes should also be praised for his brilliant glovework.
Tossed up and wide outside off, Kohli drives it through the covers and gets two. The 50-run stand is up between the two and the lead now reads 351. And with this, IT IS LUNCH ON DAY 3.
Floated on middle, Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Kohli has been warned for running on the pitch. He isn't pleased and has a word with the umpire. Replays showed that while going for the third run, Kohli did change the path and went across the pitch
Too full and wide outside off. Ashwin drills it through the covers and scampers back for three more.
Floated outside off, Kohli pokes it towards backward point and gets to the other end.
Low full toss, pushed towards the extra cover region for a quick single.
Shout for a caught behind! It's not given. Joe Root thinks long and then takes the DRS. It's daylight between bat and ball. Waste of a review and one of the worst reviews ever!

NOT OUT! Well, well! Why was this reviewed? A poor one from Root and England. Big, big turn on the first ball for Lawrence though. It pitches on middle, on the rough and spins down the leg side sharply. Ashwin looks to flick but misses. They appeal for a caught behind as Foakes collects the ball but the umpire stays put. Root thinks and then takes a late review after discussing with his boys. The replays show that there was a good social distancing maintained between bat and ball.
Last over before Lunch. Root tosses the ball to Dan Lawrence. Can he do something in these 6 balls?
Around off on a good length. Kohli is rock solid in defense again.
Good length and outside off, Kohli pushes it towards the backward point fielder.
Outside off again. Kohli lets it be.
Back of a length and around off, Kohli is solid in defense.
Good length and around off, poked towards backward point. Wanted a single but Ashwin was not interested.
Outside off, left alone. Good take from Foakes behind the sticks. It was to his right and went a bit high too.
Floated on middle and leg, Ashwin blocks.
Full again. It is pushed to long on for an easy single. With men in the deep, easy singles on offer at the moment.

FOUR! Nicely done! Full and on the pads, Kohli clips it through short fine leg and it races away to the fence. Didn't hit it too hard but the outfield is quick. The fielder gives it a chase but the ball wins the races.
Floated around off, Kohli is solid in defense.
On off, poked towards backward point for one this time.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket for nothing.
Bounce this time and Kohli is beaten on the outside edge. Good stuff from Broad. Shortish and just outside off, a hint of away movement. Kohli fails to defend. Foakes cannot gather it cleanly too.

EDGED BUT PUT DOWN! That flew to Stokes and he fails to snap it. It was the cutter from Broad, landed around off and went away as Ashwin looked to drive. The outside edge flew to the left of Stokes who reacted at first slip but failed to hold on. It deflected away and the batsmen crossed.
Around off on a length, kept out.
Good length and around off, poked towards point.
Full and outside off, pushed to the man at backward point.

FOUR! A length ball around middle, Ashwin clips it through short fine leg. The deep square leg fielder runs in and puts in a diving effort. The Indians take three. The third umpire is called to confirm if it is a clean stop. Looks like Leach is touching the rope at the time when he tries to push the ball back in. Yes, a boundary is given. So, Broad is welcomed into the attack with a boundary.
Well, well! Stuart Broad is playing this game as well. And he gets his opportunity for the first time in this innings. Foakes is up to the stumps.

Now on the front foot. This is good from the Indian skipper. Leach tosses it up and bowls it outside off. Kohli comes on the front foot, smothers the spin and bunts it on the off side. Proper Test cricket style batting from the Indian skipper on this testing track.
This time Kohli stays back as Leach drops it slightly short. It's kept out safely on the off side.
Another solid front foot block from Kohli as Leach bowls this one around off.
Defends it solidly this time.
Loopy and outside off, poked towards the off side.
Big appeal but turned down. No review from England. Floated around off, Virat comes on the front foot and looks to defend but probably gets an inside edge on the pad.
Floated outside off, kept out.
FOUR! Ashwin connects the sweep again. This is top stuff from him. He moves to 24 off 26 balls. Tossed up and around middle, Ashwin nails the sweep over the man at short fine leg for a boundary.
Too full and on middle, Kohli flicks it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Flat and around middle, flicked to mid-wicket for nothing.
Floated outside off, Kohli moves across on the off side and blocks.
Flat and just around off, kept out.
Turn and bounce and Ashwin is beaten as he lunges in defense. This will keep happening on this surface.
Flat and on middle, this time he flicks it through square leg. Two taken. Ashwin moves to 20 off just 24 balls. Playing a gem!
FOUR! Swept and swept hard. Loopy and outside off, Ashwin gets down and nails the sweep through square leg. Plays it against the turn and finds the fence again. His 3rd boundary.
Tossed up and just around off, Ashwin backs away and looks to go inside out but ends up getting it high on the bat. It lobs towards the bowler but falls short.
Again very full and around off, pushed towards the cover region once more.
Very full and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Ashwin sweeps it hard again but finds square leg who fumbles and they take one.
Floated around off, Ashwin comes on the front foot to block it safely.
Darted on the pad, blocked nicely.
On off, kept out.
Tossed up and on middle, Ashwin sweeps it hard. The man at square leg dives to his left but fails to stop. The fielder in the deep cuts it off and the batsmen take two.
Almost dragged on! Flat and just outside off, spins in sharply. Ashwin gets an inside edge that goes past the stumps to leg slip.
Kohli stays back and eases it towards backward point. He is off for the single but Ashwin says no.

This time Ashwin is to the pitch of the ball and lofts it over the man at mid on. Broad gives it a chase and puts in a fine sliding stop. Saves a run for his side, does Broad. Haven't got a chance to bowl but Broad is doing his best in the field.
Goes for the sweep this time but this one sneaks below his bat and goes to the keeper. It was pitched outside off and Ashwin made no connection as it went straight on.
This time it keeps low and it is outside off. Ashwin does well to block.
Pokes this one towards backward point and gets to the other end.
Beaten! Floated outside off, spins away. Kohli is on the front foot to block but misses. Good take from Foakes behind the sticks. The birthday boy is having a good time.
Uppish but safe! Ashwin wanted to work it on the leg side but it came slower through the air. Ends up getting a leading edge which falls to the left of the bowler.
Full and around off, pushed to mid off. Wanted a single but opted against it.
Short and around middle, kept out off the front foot to mid off.
This time he flicks it wide of the man at mid-wicket and takes one.
Full again. This one is on middle and leg. Flicked towards mid-wicket.
Floats the first ball full and around off, Kohli blocks.
Here's skipper Joe Root with the ball.
Floated around off, kept out.
This is darted outside off. Ashwin lets it be. Watches it all the way to the gloves of the keeper.
Once again he stays back as Leach drops it short and pokes it wide of the backward point fielder. This time they get the run.
Pitches and turns away. Kohli stays back and taps it towards backward point. Kohli thinks for the single but no says his partner at the other end.
Floated around off, Kohli is on the front foot to block.
FOUR! BANG! Poor from Leach this time. Short and wide outside off, Kohli rocks back and thumps it through point to bag a boundary now. Runs flowing for India at the moment.

FOUR! Ashwin brings the reverse sweep now and bags another boundary. Tossed up and outside off, Ashwin plays the unconventional sweep and top edges it over short third man. The man from the ring gives it a chase and pulls it back as the batters take three. The third umpire has been called. And it has been given as a boundary. Stokes, the man who put in that effort, looks unhappy.
Flat and around middle, clipped to mid-wicket this time.
On off, looks to drive this time but the ball spins in, takes the inner half and goes to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Broom is out and the crowd loves it. It is the local boy. Tossed up and outside off, Ashwin gets down and nails the sweep through the mid-wicket region. Lovely shot to get off the mark.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
The local boy, Ravichandran Ashwin, is in now and he is welcomed with a huge cheer.

The finger has gone up! Axar Patel is out lbw! He wants to get it reviewed though. It seems that only an inside edge can save him. NO BAT INVOLVED, confirms the Ultra Edge. Umpire's call on hitting the stumps. Patel has to go.

OUT! LBW! No bat involved and umpire's call on hitting wickets. The onfield call stays and India lose their sixth wicket. Lovely from Leach. He slowed this one down and landed it around off. Patel comes on the front foot to defend but a hint of spin into the batsman means he misses to get struck on the pad. A loud appeal and the umpire raises his finger after taking a bit of time. Axar has a word with the skipper and decides to take it upstairs. Time for the replays. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that the ball would clip the middle stump. So, Patel has to go. Review stays for the Indians though as it was the umpire's call.
FOUR! And he won't miss out on the scoring opportunity. Leach bowls a full toss on the pads, Kohli whips it through square leg and finds the fence. The lead goes up to 301.
Beaten! But got to give it to Kohli for not chasing the spin. He stays back and allows the ball to turn and then looks to defend. Misses but is beaten by some distance.
Full and around off, kept out.
Goes on the back foot and blocks it towards the off side again.
Floated around off, Kohli pokes it towards the cover region off the front foot.
Flat and just outside off, Kohli stays back to block.
FOUR! 100 up for India! Slightly short and on middle, turning away, Axar goes on the back foot, uses his wrists and whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, Patel defends it from the middle of the bat.
And again, Patel is beaten as he fails to deal with the delivery spinning away from his willow.
Another play and a miss! Spinning away from around off, Patel gets back and pushes at it but it turns to beat the blade.
Turning away from the batsman, Axar is beaten as he tries to defend off the front foot.
Flighted and full around off, Patel defends it off the front foot.
Nicely flighted and full on middle, Virat leans forward and defends it close to his front pad.
Flatter and shorter on middle, Axar gets the chance to go back and help it behind square leg for a run.
Uses his feet this time and flicks a full ball across the line, finds short mid-wicket.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Beaten! Patel looks to defend it with the spin but this one goes straight on to beat the outside edge.
Flighted and full on off, Axar is forward as he works it with the spin to short mid-wicket.

Drinks break! The first hour has entirely belonged to England. Four wickets in it and they have spoiled India's plans of scoring quick runs this morning. The pitch is looking extremely tough to bat on and India already have a lead close to 300. So despite a shaky start to Day 3, they remain in the driver's seat. England are doing what they can do best but their batting in the first innings is going to haunt them, conceding a lead of 195-run on this surface has almost shut the door on their face.
On the pads, this time Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but misses.
Dropped short again. This time he goes deep in the crease to work it towards the leg side.
Floated outside off, spinning in. Kohli comes on the front foot and manages to tuck it towards short fine leg.
Short and outside off, tucked towards the leg side.
Floated outside off, Axar comes on the front foot to defend. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the short third man region. Quick single taken.
Full and on middle, kept out.
Flicks this one towards mid-wicket and says no for the run. A good over for the Indians. 10 off the over.

FOUR! BOOM! Shot of the morning. Kohli finding is mojo here. Tossed up and on middle, Kohli uses the bottom hand and whips it through mid on for a boundary. The man at mid on had no chance to react to his left.
Loopy and around off, Kohli is on the front foot to dead bat it.
Short and just outside off, Kohli goes on the back foot and flicks it through mid-wicket. The long on fielder gives it a chase and stops it near the fence. Two for Kohli.
Floated outside off, Patel looks to drive but it goes to mid-wicket off the inner half. A single taken.
First bad ball from Leach and Kohli is onto it in a flash. Punches it through backward point and gets three. Kohli is into the double digits.
Full and around off, kept out safely off the front foot. End of another successful over for England.
Short and just outside off, Patel punches it well but finds the cover fielder.
Floated around off, kept out off the front foot.
Axar Patel, the debutant, strides out to the middle now. Two slips in place. Pope at short leg.

OUT! TAKEN! Fine catch at short leg and Rahane walks back now. Moeen gets his first wicket. Half the Indian team back to the pavilion now. Moeen slows this one and lands it outside off. Rahane comes down the track to defend with his bat and pad together. This one doesn't turn much and Rahane ends up getting it off the inner half of the bat. It then hits his pad and lobs uppishly in front of Pope at short leg. The master of short leg catching, Pope, dives forward and takes the catch inches above the turf. The umpire raises his finger and Rahane goes. India lead by 281 at the moment.
On middle, kept out.
Tossed up and outside off. Rahane comes down the track and makes it into a full toss. Pushes it towards the cover region in the end.
Flat and around off, turns in. Kohli stays back to defend.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! Kohli will take it. Floated outside off, Kohli comes on the front foot and looks to defend but with soft hands. The ball takes the outer half and goes past the man at backward point. Stone gives it a chase, reaches out with a slide but ends up pushing it into the fence at third man as he tries to pick up the ball. Poor work.
Darted outside off, left alone.
On off, kept out.
Leading edge! Floated full delivery and around off, Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but it takes the leading edge and goes uppishly past the man at silly point.
Floated around off, poked towards backward point.
Good ball to end the over! Draws the batsman forward with a loopy ball. It spins in and Rahane is hit high on the pad.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries to Rahane and India. After a full toss, Moeen drags his length short and around middle and leg. Rahane rocks back and hammers the pull through square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Freebie from Moeen and Rahane will not miss out. A full toss just around off, Rahane takes a step forward and nails it through the covers to find the fence. Poor from Moeen.
Big, big turn! Like a cobra this one. It pitches short and outside off. Lands on a rough and spins in sharply. Rahane goes on the back foot and somehow manages to fend it off.
Looped up and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Floated outside off, Rahane takes a long stride forward and looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. The impact is well outside off so no appeal.
Flat and around off, kept out off the back foot.
Rahane goes for the sweep this time. Fails to connect it off the middle and it goes towards the leg side off the inner half. A single taken.

Uppish but safe! Burns flew to his left and maybe got fingertips to it. Tossed up and outside off, Kohli drives it uppishly. The ball goes wide of the man at covers who dives to his left but fails to catch. Three taken as the ball stops nears the fence.
On off, Kohli comes on the front foot to block.
Full ball around off, pushed to the cover region.
Edgy! Shortish and just outside off, Rahane rocks back and looks to cut but ends up getting an under edge. It hits the pad of the keeper and goes to mid-wicket. A single taken.
Quicker and around off, worked on the leg side.
Floated around off, pushed to mid off.

FOUR LEG BYES! Welcome boundary for India. This one turns in, Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but it keeps low. Hits his pad and races away to the fence at fine leg. That came off the bat clearly as the replays suggested but given leg byes by the umpire.
Short ball, slower through the air. It is outside off. Kohli pulls it hard but cannot beat the man at mid-wicket.
Full and around off, Kohli whips it using his bottom hand but finds mid on.
Tossed up and around off, spins in. Kohli comes on the front foot to block.

Just short! Rahane would've had his heart in his mouth. This one was short and it spun away. Rahane looks to cut but fails to connect it well. It goes uppishly to Stone at backward point but it falls short. Eventful over ends.
Rahane is beaten this time. Pitches just outside off and spins away as Rahane looks to block off the front foot.
Full and around off, Rahane looks to defend but it goes off the inner half to mid-wicket.
Ajinkya Rahane, the Indian vice-captain, joins Virat Kohli in the middle.

OUT! STUMPED! Foakes with a stunning work again and Pant falls now. He was always going to play his shot but falls in the process. Leach tosses it up and outside off, Pant dances down the track but fails to reach to the pitch properly. And the ball lands in the rough and spins in to beat his attempt. It goes to the right side of  Foakes who collects the ball and whips the bails in a flash. Pant walks back now and the morning keeps getting better.

FOUR! Not where he wanted to hit but Pant will take it. First boundary of the morning. Tossed up and outside off, Pant gets down and looks to sweep. The ball spins in. It takes the gloves and goes to the right side of the keeper. Races away to the fine leg fence.
Quicker one on middle, tucked towards square leg.
Floated around off, Kohli comes on the front foot to defend solidly.
He is off the mark on the 20th ball. A flat ball around off, spinning in. Kohli this time goes on the back foot and tucks it through short fine leg for a brace.
Fuller and around off and middle, worked towards the same fielder again.
On middle, flicked towards square leg.
Turn again! Pitches around off and spins in. Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but misses.
Good running! Flat and around off, turns away. Pant pokes it towards the off side. Kohli calls for the single. Pant responds and they get it easily in the end.
Flat and around middle, Kohli flicks it to the man at square leg.
Beats him this time with the one that lands on the rough around off and turns away. Kohli was on the front foot to defend.
Loopy and around off, Kohli is on the front foot to block.
Looped up outside off, turning away. Kohli lets it be.
Full and on middle, Kohli flicks it nicely but once again finds the fielder. This time it goes to square leg.
Loopy ball outside off, Kohli drives but finds mid off. 11 balls and nothing for the Indian skipper so far.
On middle and leg and shortish in length. Pant goes back and works it towards the leg side.
Pant wanted to come down the track and adjusted in the end as Moeen darted a flat one around off. Pant defends.
Shortish and just outside off, turns away. Pant waits and punches it towards backward point. Thinks for a single but Kohli says no.
On middle and leg, pushed back to the bowler this time.
In the air... safe! It was a full toss on middle, Pant goes for the sweep but ends up miscuing it. It goes wide of the man at short fine leg. Two taken.
Quicker one around the pad on a slightly shorter length. Pant defends off the back foot.
This one is flat and just outside off. Kohli goes back to punch it on the off side. End of a successful over for England and Leach.
Loopy and just outside off, long stride forward again and a solid block.
Comes on the front foot and solidly blocks.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
He is off the mark in a streaky fashion. Floated just around off, it spins away. Pant looks to force it on the off side but it takes the outer half and goes through backward point for one.
Oh, hello! Who is in now? Rishabh Pant it is. Facing Leach first up.

OUT! STUMPED! Very sharp work from Foakes and England have sent both the overnight Indian batters back to the pavilion. Superb delivery from Leach. Rohit walks back now. Leach tosses the ball just outside off, Rohit lunges forward and looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge. Foakes collects and takes the bails off in a flash. The third umpire has been called for again. And Rohit's foot is on the line, feels the third umpire. Nothing behind the line and OUT flashes on the big screen. The centurion from the first innings has to go.
Stumping appeal! Ben Foakes has been really busy this morning. Is the back foot on the line?
Once again a solid front foot defense presented by the Indian skipper. Good, testing over from Moeen again.
Tossed up and outside off, kept out.
Short but slower through the air. Kohli is early in the pull to miss out on a scoring opportunity.
This time Moeen loops it up. Kohli comes on the front foot and bunts it onto the pitch.
Sharp spin. It lands on the rough and spins in. Kohli looks to defend but misses to get hit on the body.
Flat and around off, spins in. Kohli comes on the front foot to block.
This time he takes a big stride forward and defends solidly.
Fullish and on middle, Rohit flicks uppishly towards mid-wicket.
On off, Rohit is solid in defense.
Loops up around off, turns away. Rohit looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge. Stokes dives to his right to stop the ball.
Floated on middle, Rohit comes on the front foot to block.
Tossed up on middle, tucked towards short fine leg.
Kohli, Kohli goes the crowd. Yes, the Indian skipper is in now. Jack Leach will partner Moeen Ali from the other end.

OUT! RUN OUT! Pujara is short. Oh, dear! What an unfortunate way to get dismissed. You got to feel for Pujara. His bat got stuck in the crease and he failed to return back. Moment of luck for England early in the morning. Moeen loops it up and around off and middle, Pujara comes down the track and flicks. Pope at short leg is alert. He stops the ball quickly and throws it to the keeper who takes the bails off. The third umpire has been called for. Replays roll in. Pujara tries to get back but his bat gets stuck in the crease and then he tries to return but ends up being on the line. And that is enough for the third umpire to send him back to the pavilion. Unfortunate way to get dismissed.

Referral for run out! It's against Pujara. Seems like an unfortunate dismissal. Cheteshwar tries to drag his bat in but it gets stuck just outside the crease as he loses control. Tries to step inside the crease but the replays show that it's aerial and Foakes as dislodged the bails. Lucky breakthrough for England.
Floated around off, Pujara defends it nicely.
Flat and around off, kept out.
This time Pujara dances down the track and works it towards square leg. Rohit says no for the run.
Turn but the line is not right. Moeen once again lands it around middle, it spins in and beats the flick of Pujara.
Run straightaway! Ali floats the first ball on middle, it spins in a touch. Rohit clips it through square leg for a single.

On the debate regarding the pitch, here is what Sunil Gavaskar has to say! The Little Master says that the pitch is not easy to play but it's not as bad as it is made to look. He gives the example of Rohit's knock and feels that you should not blame the pitch if you don't have the skills to play the turning ball. Adds that the batsmen should bat forward and look to smother the spin.

Right! Let's go again. The two umpires stride out to the middle and the England players take the field too. Rohit Sharma and Cheteshwar Pujara make their way out as well. Spin to start from England this morning. Moeen Ali, it is. Slip and forward short leg in place. Here we go...

Pitch report - Mark Butcher from the studio says that the wicket is crumbling more. Feels things will get even better for the spinners. Adds that the England spinners will have to look at how the Indian spinners have exploited the surface to their effect. Tells that they need to bowl a tad fuller on this wicket.

India are leading by 249 at the moment and they have 9 wickets in the kitty. Rohit Sharma is looking in solid touch and he has got Pujara for company. You know how Rohit can hit and you know how long Pujara can bat. England bowlers or we shall say the England spinners will look to use the surface to their advantage and strike early to keep the scoring rate under check as well.  So, we are in for another scintillating day of Test match cricket.

Hello and welcome to the moving day of the Test match. When you see 15 wickets fall on the second day of the Test match, you already know the Test has moved along really quickly. And when you know most of the discussions going around is about the wicket, you more or less know which team is on top.
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

Right! That's all from Day 2 from this game. The game has moved very quickly and we might see an early finish. And the way things have gone, Day 3 can well be the final day of the game. Do join us for the moving day of the Test on Monday, 15th February 2021 which begins at 0930 local (0400 GMT). Until then, it is goodbye from our end. Cheers and take care!

Earlier in the day, India lost their 4 wickets in quick time with Pant remaining unbeaten on 58. Moeen and Stone got two apiece to close the Indian innings. Indians responded superbly and removed the 4 top order batters with the score not even crossing 50. And that included the big wicket of Root as well. It was the combined effort from the Indian bowlers as Ishant got them the first wicket and Ashwin and Axar combined to get the other three wickets. Ben Stokes didn't last long as Ashwin went through his defense in the 2nd session. In that session, Foakes along with Pope presented a little fight but once Pope was strangled down the leg side, England fell apart, losing 4 wickets in the session. England managed to avoid the follow-on with Foakes and Leach battling hard. However, the Indians didn't take long to close the innings and take a big lead of 195.

After bundling England in this session, Rohit and Gill gave India a bright start. They attacked the bowling and went for runs. The openers added 42 before Gill departed. Rohit along with Pujara made sure there wasn't another blip for the Indians. It was Leach who got the wicket for England. The spinners did manage a lot of purchase off the surface but the Indians didn't allow them an opening.
Another fantastic phase for India as they have extended their lead to 249 and still have 9 wickets left and push England further on the back foot. Overall, a superb day for the hosts.
Floated around off, Pujara comes on the front foot to bunt it on the leg side. With that, it is STUMPS ON DAY 2.
One ball to go. And Pujara is not happy with something in front of the sightscreen. Interesting.
Shortish and around middle, Pujara stays back to block it.

Last over before Stumps. Rohit and Pujara are having a discussion in the middle. Root is having a chat with his bowler.
Turn again! This one pitches outside off, spins in. Pujara is down the track to defend. Misses to get hit on the pad and it lobs on the off side. A mild appeal but turned down.
Shortish and around off, this time it is pushed towards the cover region.
On the pads, Pujara pads it away.
On off, pushed to mid off this time.

Foakes collects and takes the bails off quickly. They appeal and the third umpire has been called for. Replays roll in and it shows that Rohit's back leg is in.
Stumping appeal taken upstairs. Rohit has his back leg grounded.
Outside off, left alone.
